job_detail:
Core member of the Company Management Team as the strategic partner to support decision making and develop business strategies, to exercise full spectrum of finance responsibilities covering accounting, reporting, taxation, treasury, legal, insurance, IT, and compliance.

1.	Business Partnering:
-	Actively participate in business strategy developments;
-	Develop constructive financial analysis for business decisions and to achieve the business goals and objectives;
-	Support General Manager to ensure full compliance with the local laws and Group directives;
-	Support General Manger to improve and to develop robust internal control workflows, processes and procedures;
-	Lead business planning, outlook, forecasting and annual budgeting.
-	Support General Manager to optimize net working capital;
-	Monitor and track project executions, in the areas of revenue recognition, gross margin, cash position, taxation, legal, Insurance and risk management.
-	As a gatekeeper of the company in terms of risk management.
-	Active and professional cooperation with management team

2.	Financial Functions
-	Ensure smooth financial closings every month;
-	Lead the finance team to deliver accurate and timely monthly financial reporting, quarterly forecasting and annual budget;
-	Ensure proper payment and cash flow management;
-	Ensure accurate balance sheet reporting;
-	Ensure proper tax reporting and filing to the local tax bureaus;
-	Lead the finance team to ensure proper custodian of fixed assets, general assets and inventory;
-	Lead the finance team to implement approved business strategies and to track the action progress;
-	Manage the annual statutory and group audits. 

3.	Team Management
-	High leadership quality and management skills as people manager
-	Enhance team quality via on-the-job training and coaching.
-	Develop proper job rotation and succession planning.

4.	IT (dotted line manager in local)
-	Support closely with the Global and Regional IT to complete IT projects and tasks as per Group IT roadmap.
-	Lead the local IT team members to ensure smooth operation of the ERP and other system.
-	Local IT’s administrative supervisor
